"{\"uid\": \"meetings.skift.com-2024-07-03-la-convention-center-expansion-approved-ahead-of-2028-olympics\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Los Angeles is now on track to unveil a major convention center expansion, just in time for the LA28 Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 107, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 11, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999951805876, \"rank\": 3.827334552034972e-09, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"track\", \"from\": 22, \"to\": 27}, {\"ngram\": \"a major convention center expansion\", \"from\": 38, \"to\": 73}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 83, \"to\": 87}, {\"ngram\": \"the LA28 Games\", \"from\": 92, \"to\": 106}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Select a question above orask something else On Tuesday, the Los Angeles City Councilapprovedthe Los Angeles Convention Center (LACC) Expansion and Modernization Project.\", \"from\": 109, \"to\": 280, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a question\", \"from\": 116, \"to\": 126}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 139, \"to\": 148}, {\"ngram\": \"Tuesday\", \"from\": 157, \"to\": 164}, {\"ngram\": \"LACC) Expansion and Modernization Project\", \"from\": 237, \"to\": 278}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Construction is planned to start in spring 2025 and be completed before the 2028 Olympic and Paralympic Games start.\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 397, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Construction\", \"from\": 281, \"to\": 293}, {\"ngram\": \"spring\", \"from\": 317, \"to\": 323}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2028 Olympic and Paralympic Games\", \"from\": 353, \"to\": 390}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The City of Los Angeles owns the LACC, which is managed byASM Global.\", \"from\": 399, \"to\": 468, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 432, \"end\": 436, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_College\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LACC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_College\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_College\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The City\", \"from\": 399, \"to\": 407}, {\"ngram\": \"Los Angeles\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 422}, {\"ngram\": \"byASM Global\", \"from\": 455, \"to\": 467}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The venue hosts almost 200 meetings and events and attracts 2 million visitors annually.\", \"from\": 469, \"to\": 557, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The venue\", \"from\": 469, \"to\": 478}, {\"ngram\": \"almost 200 meetings\", \"from\": 485, \"to\": 504}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 509, \"to\": 515}, {\"ngram\": \"2 million visitors\", \"from\": 529, \"to\": 547}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The expansion includes adding 190,000 square feet to connect the South and West Exhibit Halls, creating one contiguous hall.\", \"from\": 559, \"to\": 683, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The expansion\", \"from\": 559, \"to\": 572}, {\"ngram\": \"190,000 square feet\", \"from\": 589, \"to\": 608}, {\"ngram\": \"the South and West Exhibit Halls\", \"from\": 620, \"to\": 652}, {\"ngram\": \"one contiguous hall\", \"from\": 663, \"to\": 682}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It will also add 55,000 square feet of new meeting room space and 95,000 square feet of multipurpose space.\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 791, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"55,000 square feet\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 719}, {\"ngram\": \"new meeting room space\", \"from\": 723, \"to\": 745}, {\"ngram\": \"95,000 square feet\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 768}, {\"ngram\": \"multipurpose space\", \"from\": 772, \"to\": 790}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The plan also features a redesign of Gilbert Lindsay Plaza, introducing public open space and an outdoor event venue.\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 909, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 829, \"end\": 844, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gilbert_W._Lindsay\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gilbert Lindsay\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gilbert_W._Lindsay\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gilbert_W._Lindsay\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The plan\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 800}, {\"ngram\": \"a redesign\", \"from\": 815, \"to\": 825}, {\"ngram\": \"public open space\", \"from\": 864, \"to\": 881}, {\"ngram\": \"an outdoor event venue\", \"from\": 886, \"to\": 908}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The L.A. City Council projects that the expansion will create 7,445 jobs during construction and 2,147 ongoing jobs.\", \"from\": 911, \"to\": 1027, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 915, \"end\": 919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999998060503, \"rank\": 1.9043442982777324e-10, \"text\": \"L.A.\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 920, \"end\": 932, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_Council\", \"score\": 0.9998901221995404, \"rank\": 7.618198468256291e-05, \"text\": \"City Council\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q11204\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_Council\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_Council\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the expansion\", \"from\": 947, \"to\": 960}, {\"ngram\": \"7,445 jobs\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 983}, {\"ngram\": \"construction\", \"from\": 991, \"to\": 1003}, {\"ngram\": \"2,147 ongoing jobs\", \"from\": 1008, \"to\": 1026}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Once concluded, projections point to the expansion generating $165 million in additional revenue from the 50,000 additional attendee days annually, equating to an increase of $30 million ($570 million over 30 years) to the city's general fund tax revenue.\", \"from\": 1028, \"to\": 1283, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"projections\", \"from\": 1044, \"to\": 1055}, {\"ngram\": \"the expansion\", \"from\": 1065, \"to\": 1078}, {\"ngram\": \"additional revenue\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1124}, {\"ngram\": \"the 50,000 additional attendee days\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1165}, {\"ngram\": \"an increase\", \"from\": 1188, \"to\": 1199}, {\"ngram\": \"30 years\", \"from\": 1234, \"to\": 1242}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's general fund tax revenue\", \"from\": 1247, \"to\": 1282}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a jointstatementfrom the Los Angeles City Tourism Department, the Los Angeles Convention Center and the Los Angeles Tourism & Convention Board, the city acknowledges its current competitive disadvantage.\", \"from\": 1285, \"to\": 1491, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1317, \"end\": 1329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angeles_City\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Angeles City\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angeles_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Angeles_City\"}, {\"begin\": 1354, \"end\": 1383, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Convention_Center\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Los Angeles Convention Center\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Convention_Center\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_Convention_Center\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a jointstatementfrom\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1308}, {\"ngram\": \"the Los Angeles Tourism\", \"from\": 1388, \"to\": 1411}, {\"ngram\": \"Convention Board\", \"from\": 1414, \"to\": 1430}, {\"ngram\": \"the city\", \"from\": 1432, \"to\": 1440}, {\"ngram\": \"its current competitive disadvantage\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1490}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Los Angeles has been at a competitive disadvantage in attracting large, citywide conventions due to the lack of contiguous space, especially as competitors have completed or are in the process of completing major expansions.\\\"\", \"from\": 1492, \"to\": 1718, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1493, \"end\": 1504, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999951805876, \"rank\": 3.827334552034972e-09, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a competitive disadvantage\", \"from\": 1517, \"to\": 1543}, {\"ngram\": \"large, citywide conventions\", \"from\": 1558, \"to\": 1585}, {\"ngram\": \"the lack\", \"from\": 1593, \"to\": 1601}, {\"ngram\": \"contiguous space\", \"from\": 1605, \"to\": 1621}, {\"ngram\": \"competitors\", \"from\": 1637, \"to\": 1648}, {\"ngram\": \"the process\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1685}, {\"ngram\": \"major expansions\", \"from\": 1700, \"to\": 1716}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Council has selected a public-private partnership model, also referred to as P3, which incorporates designing, building, financing, operating, and maintaining in one model.\", \"from\": 1720, \"to\": 1896, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1801, \"end\": 1803, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Integrated_Truss_Structure\", \"score\": 0.44388821931287126, \"rank\": 0.7651794541017118, \"text\": \"P3\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Integrated_Truss_Structure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Integrated_Truss_Structure\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Council\", \"from\": 1720, \"to\": 1731}, {\"ngram\": \"a public-private partnership model\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1779}, {\"ngram\": \"designing\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1833}, {\"ngram\": \"building\", \"from\": 1835, \"to\": 1843}, {\"ngram\": \"financing\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1854}, {\"ngram\": \"operating\", \"from\": 1856, \"to\": 1865}, {\"ngram\": \"one model\", \"from\": 1886, \"to\": 1895}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This model involves contracting with a joint venture of AEG and The Plenary Group.\", \"from\": 1897, \"to\": 1979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1953, \"end\": 1956, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.551249158726022e-19, \"text\": \"AEG\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\"}, {\"begin\": 1965, \"end\": 1978, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plenary_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Plenary Group\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plenary_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Plenary_Group\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This model\", \"from\": 1897, \"to\": 1907}, {\"ngram\": \"a joint venture\", \"from\": 1934, \"to\": 1949}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The P3 model was selected over a \\\"construction manager at risk\\\" model, which would have been financed entirely by the City of Los Angeles through city-issued long-term debt.\", \"from\": 1981, \"to\": 2154, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1985, \"end\": 1987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Integrated_Truss_Structure\", \"score\": 0.44388821931287126, \"rank\": 0.7651794541017118, \"text\": \"P3\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Integrated_Truss_Structure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Integrated_Truss_Structure\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a \\\"construction manager\", \"from\": 2012, \"to\": 2035}, {\"ngram\": \"risk\\\" model\", \"from\": 2039, \"to\": 2050}, {\"ngram\": \"the City\", \"from\": 2095, \"to\": 2103}, {\"ngram\": \"Los Angeles\", \"from\": 2107, \"to\": 2118}, {\"ngram\": \"city-issued long-term debt\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2153}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The rejected model would have delayed development by six months, making using the LACC during the LA28 Games impossible.\", \"from\": 2155, \"to\": 2275, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2237, \"end\": 2241, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_College\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LACC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_College\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles_City_College\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The rejected model\", \"from\": 2155, \"to\": 2173}, {\"ngram\": \"development\", \"from\": 2193, \"to\": 2204}, {\"ngram\": \"six months\", \"from\": 2208, \"to\": 2218}, {\"ngram\": \"the LA28 Games\", \"from\": 2249, \"to\": 2263}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, operating costs were projected to be approximately $5 million less annually.\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2361, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"operating costs\", \"from\": 2285, \"to\": 2300}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In October, LA Tourism formed aunique partnershipwith AEG, a sister company to ASM Global.\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2453, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2417, \"end\": 2420, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.551249158726022e-19, \"text\": \"AEG\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\"}, {\"begin\": 2442, \"end\": 2452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.467893427621576e-42, \"text\": \"ASM Global\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anschutz_Entertainment_Group\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"October\", \"